name: The West Tatras
description: Although it was still morning, the Tatra Mountains were already strongly illuminated by the sun. In the upper right hand corner, is the summit of the Horse Peak. Although it appears delicate, it is over 2000 metres above sea level. The West Tatras, although they are called the land of gentleness, are demanding mountains because of their height, but especially because of the long distances that have to be travelled between peaks.
